    <h2>Results</h2>
    <p>The gearbox functioned smoothly under unloaded conditions, with minimal backlash and consistent gear alignment during hand-driven testing. Although no load testing was performed at this stage, the proof-of-concept validates the fitment and movement integrity. Load testing and dynamic trials are planned for future stages once associated mechanical systems are brought online.</p>

    <h2>Tools & Technologies Used</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Fusion 360 (gear design, assembly modeling)</li>
      <li>FDM 3D Printer (PLA, 0.4mm nozzle)</li>
      <li>Calipers for tolerance checks</li>
      <li>Custom CAD-based fitment testing</li>
    </ul>
